narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: In this course, I have improved my self-management skills and learned knowledge. I had to make a plan to finish my work on time and study for this course, which improved my knowledge understanding, and self-management skills.
I learnt a lot about calculus, and calculation skills.
I have learned great deep insights into differentiation and calculus as well as learned strong reasoning of why a specific solving method is used.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments:
Strengths: There are plenty of practice questions, which I could test my knowledge and understanding.
Weakness: It is a very intensive course, and sometimes it is hard to understand by watching videos. 
How: More class time.

Before choosing the course I didn't know how much of personal study time would be required and I only found out during the course that i order to excel, you have to complete around 5 hours of individual study prior the lessons as well as about 2 hours for the homework. I would have preferred more zoom tutorials and less frequent assignments.
The class was overall really interesting with some fun quizzes before the class.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes, because it helps us to improve our self-skills and knowledge understanding of calculus.
Yes. it is a great math course.
Yes, although I would warn them about the great workload and the grand amount of personal study time required.

narratives.question_text: The Canvas course site allowed me to identify and access required course materials easily.
How will you use the knowledge and skills you learned in this course in your future endeavors?
comments: In terms of self-management skills, I could use them in a variety of ways in the future since it helps me to manage my time to finish other long-term projects.  In terms of Knowledge, I could study it in advance since I will have to learn it after 1 year.
I would use my knowledge to help me learn my A-level maths content more easily this academic year.
To take other challenging courses in calculus
